  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="DA">Improved Food Security through introduction of Farmer Family Learning Group in Organic Agriculture in Assuokow and Odumasi</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="DA">The main focus of this project is improved food security for the largest groups of small holder subsistence farmers in the Assuokow-Odumase and its environs. We have experienced that organic agriculture, understood as farming to the principles of health, care, ecology and fairness, and the conscious use of agro-ecological methods, is a highly relevant approach for improved food security in this region.Organic agriculture and the Millennium Goals. Organic production has the potential to produce sufficient food of high quality. g Group in Organic Agriculture in Assuokow and Odumase</narrative>
  </description>
